# Telemetry Ingestion & Trust Flow — PoWV Protocol

The PoWV (Proof of Weighted Value) Protocol transforms raw, trusted industrial telemetry into independently verifiable digital evidence through a hardware-assisted, layered trust architecture[cite: 2].

---

## Logical Processing Flow

1. Edge Device: Captures trusted industrial telemetry from physical infrastructure[cite: 2].
2. Secure Gateway: Performs secure ingestion, validation, and preprocessing of events.
3. Verification Layer: Produces verifiable digital evidence and integrity proofs[cite: 2].
4. Evidence Registry: Maintains immutable records for independent auditability[cite: 2].

---

## Core Design Principles

* Hardware-Assisted Trust: Establishes secure hardware enclaves as the root of trust[cite: 2].
* Verifiable Telemetry: Eliminates data silos through cryptographic proofs.
* Cryptographic Integrity: End-to-end encryption prevents any data tampering.
* End-to-End Traceability: Full historical tracking from raw sensor capturing to consensus[cite: 2].
* Modular Architecture: Pluggable design to avoid vendor lock-in.

---

NOTE: This repository represents the public research implementation of the PoWV Protocol. Production firmware configurations, specific gateway connectors, and proprietary hardware integrations are omitted for operational security[cite: 2].
